\begin_inset Formula $4(h^{-1}{\rm Gpc})^{3}$
\end_inset

 each and 64 samples in total).
 From the figure, we see that there is a correlation between the shifts
 measured for the HOD1 and HOD3 samples and its cross-correlation coefficient
 is xxx.
 On the other hand, there is little correlation for the 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

 values between HOD1 and HOD9 (where the cross-correlation coefficient is
 xxx) due to a large shot noise.
